author: Inside Edition
description: Donna Adelson is a 75-year-old grandmother accused of orchestrating the assassination of her former son-in-law, Dan Markel. The prominent, Harvard-educated professor was gunned down in his own garage. Prosecutors say Adelson paid over a hundred thousand dollars to have him killed. Donna's own son and three accomplices have already been found guilty for their roles in the murder. Adelson's lawyers are painting her as a doting, loving granny, not a cold-blooded mastermind.
title: Trial for Alleged Assassination Mastermind Grandmother Begins

author: Inside Edition
description: Beaches are public spaces, so it's legal for someone to snap photos and videos of others without their permission. But women find it very creepy. Inside Edition producers Will Evans and Emma Keady spoke to several women in Miami Beach who said being filmed without their permission was a common occurrence. Before long, they found a man perched on a pier overlooking the beach with a large telephoto lens. They watched as he appeared to zoom in on the backsides of two young women on paddleboards.
title: Inside Edition Producers Confront Man Allegedly Filming Women at Beach

author: Inside Edition
description: The case of missing seven-month-old Emmanuel Haro has taken a stunning turn. On Friday, cops swarmed the family's property and SWAT vehicles moved in, as police arrested both parents on charges of murder. Earlier this week, Emmanuel's mother Rebecca claimed she was attacked in a parking lot, and that her son was then kidnapped. But cops say her story had inconsistencies, and that she has stopped cooperating with detectives.
title: Cops Arrest Parents of Missing 7-Month-Old on Murder Charges

author: Inside Edition
description: Convicted murderer Bryan Kohberger claims he is the target of "minute-by-minute verbal threats/harassment," and wants to be moved to a different part of the Idaho prison.
title: Convicted Killer Bryan Kohberger Wants to Move to Different Prison Block #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description:
The FBI arrested a man for alleged sexual exploitation of children. Now investigators are working to find out if there are more alleged victims than what they're already aware of.

According to the FBI's Jackson office, agents are investigating Sean Gardner, who they say worked as a gymnastics coach in Mississippi, Louisiana and Iowa. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: FBI Seeks Information on Former Gymnastics Coach Accused of Crimes Against Minors

author: Inside Edition
description: Shawn Muese was posing for a picture with a shark he just caught when, in the blink of an eye, the predator bit back.
title: Shark Photo-op Goes Wrong #shorts
